ONE person has died after a house fire in Shetland.
Emergency services were called to the property in the Clousta area at around 4.15am today.
Three fire appliances attended, the Scottish Fire and Rescue Service said.
One person was found dead inside the house.
Police Scotland said they would be conducting a joint investigation with the fire service which would &quot;involve a full examination of the property and its contents&quot;.
No more details are being made available until the next of kin have been informed.
